Plan would replace structural
cohesion funds with common EU budget to enable aid to stricken
euro-area member states,  Die Welt  reported, citing unnamed EU
sources.
* Budget is priority for Chancellor  Angela Merkel  at Oct. 18-19
EU summit in Brussels
* Aims to allow joint aid for member states against economic
conditions
* Funds could flow from national budgets, transaction taxes
* France, Spain may see the proposal as diversion tactic
* Germany wants to end debate over common euro bonds with
proposal
* MORE: States could welcome suggestion, if Germany makes
concessions on areas including recapitalizing ailing banks via
the European Stability Mechanism  To contact the reporter on this story:
